vocabulary: Thu 23-04-2020 

Llevamos tiempo (tratar) de escapar de la cárcel. = We take time to escape from prison.

Estaba (pensar) en ti. = I was (think) of you.

Juanito siguió (leer). = Juanito continued (read).

Marcos lleva diez años (trabajar) aquí.  = Marcos has been working here for ten years.

repetir = to repeat

reñir (e - i) = to tell off 

La jefa sigue (ser) muy creativa cada día. = The boss is still very creative every day.

Pedro andaba (buscar) a sus amigos. = Peter walked (search) his friends.

La gente continúa (comprar) cigarrillos a pesar del precio. = People continue to (buy) cigarettes despite the price.

sugerir (e - i)= to suggest.

estoy estando = I am being

(Estar) en San Francisco, fui a saludar a mis tíos. = (to be) in San Francisco, I went to greet my uncles.

¡Mario, no andes (gritar) tanto! = Mario, don't shout so much!

La miel está (atraer) las moscas. = Honey is (to attract) flies. (atrayendo)

Estar (vivir) cerca del mar es muy conveniente para una nadadora. = Being (living) near the sea is very convenient for a swimmer.

¿Qué estabas (ver) en televisión anoche? = What were you watching on TV last night?

No te creo. Estás (mentir). (e - i) = I don't believe you. You are (lying).

Quiero continuar (vivir) en España = I want to continue (live) in Spain

Vi a mis hijos (correr) en el parque. = I saw my kids (running) in the park.

Alma estaba (cantar) en voz muy baja. = Alma was (singing) in a very low voice.

Vienen (decir) que no tienen razón. = They come (say) they are not right.

hacer = to do/ to make

Pienso que no sabes lo que estás (hacer). = I don't think you know what you're doing.

Julio está (aprender) a manejar. = Julio is (to learn) to manage.

sigamos = we follow

Quiero que sigamos (ser) amigos. = I want us to remain friends.

Cuánto  = How much 

¿Cuánto tiempo llevas (estudiar) español? = How long have you been (studying) Spanish?

Elena estaba (ir) de puerta en puerta, buscando su hija. = Elena was (going) door to door, looking for her daughter. [here 'ir' became 'yendo']

Nos estábamos (sentar) en los banquillo. = We were sitting on the bench.

Llevo veintiséis años (trabajar) aquí. = I've been working here twenty-six years.

Voy a seguir (vivir) para ser feliz. = I'm going to go on (live) to be happy.

competir (e - i) en la carrera = Competing in the race

Estaba (construir) una casa pequeña en el bosque. = It was (to build) a small house in the forest. (construir became construyendo)

Nos divertimos (cantar). = We had fun (singing).

Siguen (jugar) al béisbol todos los fines de semana. = They keep playing baseball every weekend.

Carlos estaba sentado en la cama, (pensar) en el futuro de su familia. = Charles was sitting in bed, (think) in the future of his family.

El agua está (destruir) nuestro castillo de arena. = The water is (destroy) our Castle of sand.

Mezclar bien e ir (añadir), poco a poco, la harina. = Mix well and go (add), little by little, the flour.

Los meseros están (servir) la comida. = The waiters are (serve) the food. (e - i)

¡Cuidado! El agua está (hervir). = Care! The water is (boil).

Hola hoy hice eso baile una hora,estoy mejor gracias = Hi today I did that dance an hour, I'm better thank you

wow, for an hour, that's awesome.. So what kind of dance? Salsa? = wow, por una hora, eso es impresionante.. ¿Qué clase de baile? ¿La salsa?

obra = work, book, deed

verdad = truth

razón = reason

hecho = fact, happening

pueblo = people, village

fuerza = strength, force, power

santo = saint(m)

frente = al frente facing; frente a: across from

paso = step, pace

siglo = century, age

dios = God, divinity

tierra = earth, land, ground

miedo = fear

esfuerzo = effort, endeavor

conocimiento = knowledge

suelo = ground, floor

poder = power

duda = doubt

pie = foot, base

ley = law, bill, rule

guerra = war, warfare

pesar = sorrow; a pesar de: in spite of

época = time, age, period

edad = age

medida = measure; a medida que: to the extent

fondo = bottom, end

acuerdo = accord; de acuerdo: in agreement

vista = view, sight

don = courtesy title (m), Mr., gift

orden = order; sequence (m), religious (f)

campo = field, country
